{"author":{"id":"cff9ab1d2ee9741039b2a60d90cca378a5320ba753398f6f3df8d03abcebee1b"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1772620667,"nonce":"jrziwBbW988zicQdbsRUb7FtN4s=","message":"Schema Implications:\n\nPer-department legal texts affect borrower TOS acceptance.\n\nCurrent: single tos_accepted boolean on borrowers.\nNeeded: per-department, per-version acceptance tracking.\n\nProposed tos_acceptances table:\n- borrower_id (FK) - the borrower\n- department_id (FK) - which department TOS\n- legal_text_id (FK) - which version they accepted\n- accepted_at (timestamp) - when they accepted\n\nFlow:\n1. Borrower registers once (global)\n2. First lending from Dept X: must accept Dept X TOS\n3. Dept X updates TOS: borrower must re-accept before next lending\n4. Lending from Dept Y: must accept Dept Y TOS separately\n\nLending creation checks: does the borrower have an acceptance for this departments current TOS version? If not, redirect to acceptance flow before proceeding.","files":null}]}